==Indonesian==
====abang====
'''noun'''
# elder [[brother]]

====Abang/Bang====
'''form of address'''
# [[you]] (used to address an elder brother or cousin, a male friend (who is older than oneself is), a husband or boy-friend)
Sometimes it is used with a name (Bang Samsul, Bang Amir, ...).

=====usage=====
'''Bang''' Erwin, [[mau]] [[ke]] [[mana]]?
* Erwin, where are you going?

[[Nanti]] [[malam]] [[aku]] [[ke]] [[rumah]] '''Abang'''.
* I'll come to your house tonight/this evening.


